    "title": "PHP Backend Developer (m/f/d)",
    "description": "<p><strong>Your responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>You design and develop complex, sophisticated and high-quality APIs and processes.</li>\n<li>You focus on fast and easy-to-maintain data structures and take care to deliver reliable, well-tested and sustainable code.</li>\n<li>Working closely with product management, QA and the development team, you’ll design, develop and optimise partner-oriented features for our zolar Project Center (ZPC).</li>\n<li>The development of your own skills, existing processes and development methods in the team are just as important to you as to us.</li>\n<li>You support your colleagues and you' re motivated to gain new knowledge and to share it within the team.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Your qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>You have at least 3 years of experience in software development and have successfully completed your studies with focus on IT.</li>\n<li>You’re strong using PHP 7 and frameworks such as Symfony.</li>\n<li>You have a good understanding for the development of applications in a microservice environment.</li>\n<li>Your way of working is structured, hands-on and solution-oriented.</li>\n<li>Agile development practices (TDD, BDD, pair programming, etc.) are nothing new to you.</li>\n<li>Plus: You have experience with AWS.</li>\n<li>You have a passion for learning new things and driving improvements, and you are always eager to try out new technologies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What zolar offers you</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Flexible working hours and contract of employment of indefinite duration</li>\n<li>Be part of a team that is motivated to make an impact each day</li>\n<li>Pioneer of the energy revolution to achieve a 100% renewable energies supply</li>\n<li>Plenty of room for own ideas and creative implementation of innovative solutions</li>\n<li>Our open feedback culture, we offer regular feedback discussions</li>\n<li>Numbers and goals are transparently communicated during our monthly All-Stars meeting</li>\n<li>Reduced Urban Sports Club M-membership</li>\n<li>Free energy suppliers such as fruits and drinks</li>\n<li>Our company culture, which is important to us - team events happen regularly</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Your contact person</p>\n<p>Pauline Ehrlich is looking forward to your application! Our career webpage gives you a first impression of our company culture.</p>\n",
