    "title": "Library Publishing & Repository Developer",
    "description": "<p><strong>The University of Oklahoma</strong></p>\n<p><strong>University Libraries</strong></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://libraries.ou.edu/content/jobs-ou-libraries\">Library Publishing &amp; Repository Developer</a></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Salary Range: $70,000-$80,000</strong></p>\n<p>The University of Oklahoma Libraries is seeking a Library Publishing &amp; Repository Developer. This position is primarily responsible for the development and operational administration of University of Oklahoma Libraries document repositories and library publishing platforms. Additionally, the position supports other key infrastructure underlying the OU Libraries technology strategy, and works with other members of the Cloud Infrastructure Division to cross-train and provide in-depth support across other platforms and services. The developer in this position is expected to apply a modern DevOps approach to the continuous improvement of operational practices, system reliability, and cost-effectiveness. The employment package may include the flexibility and/or expectation for a portion of work effort to be performed remotely.</p>\n<p>To see more detail about the Library Publishing &amp; Repository Developer position visit <a href=\"http://libraries.ou.edu/jobs\">libraries.ou.edu/jobs</a>. To apply for this position, go to <a href=\"https://jobs.ou.edu\">https://jobs.ou.edu</a> and search for\n<a href=\"https://ou.taleo.net/careersection/2/jobdetail.ftl?job=210111&amp;tz=GMT-06%3A00&amp;tzname=America%2FChicago\">job number 210111</a>.</p>\n<p>The University of Oklahoma, in compliance with all applicable federal and state laws and regulations, does not discriminate on the basis of race, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, genetic information, gender identity, gender expression, age, religion, disability, political beliefs, or status as a veteran in any of its policies, practices or procedures. This includes, but is not limited to: admissions, employment, financial aid and educational services. For inquiries regarding non-discrimination policies, please visit the <a href=\"http://www.ou.edu/eoo\">OU Institutional Equity Office</a>.</p>\n",
